BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Pelléas et Mélisande
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260415T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260420T143000
UID:be17fc2d0aaae01a0fd68afd1fdc2828@toronto.ca
DESCRIPTION:Rich with symbolism and dream imagery\, Pelléas et Mélisande
  is Debussy's sole opera\, and this uniquely imagined production has long 
 been a dream of Co-Artistic Directors Marshall Pynkoski and Jeannette Laje
 unesse Zingg. Based on the symbolist play by Maurice Maeterlinck\, Pelléa
 s et Mélisande follows a prince lost in a forest who discovers a beautifu
 l woman weeping beside a pool of water which brings him in contact with a 
 supernatural world from which there is no escape. Associate Music Director
  Dr. Christopher Bagan enthusiastically embraced the opportunity to realiz
 e a unique score of Debussy's massive opera in a new arrangement for Opera
  Atelier and 14 elite soloists from Tafelmusik Baroque Orchestra. Pelléas
  et Mélisande will feature David Fallis conducting and will be directed b
 y Marshall Pynko.
LOCATION:TELUS Centre for Performance and Learning at Koerner Hall\, 273 B
 loor St W\, Toronto\, ON
URL:https://www.operaatelier.com/shows/pelleas-et-melisande/
X-SOURCE:City of Toronto Festivals & Events
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Smoke Signals x Reflections
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260416T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260613T120000
UID:1220686304a8dabf07ed7f800bf19885@toronto.ca
DESCRIPTION:Visit Smoke Signals x Reflections presented by TD Bank Group a
 nd Toronto History Museums\, an exhibition where photography\, beadwork\, 
 sculpture and digital media serve as a guiding signal\, broadcasting stori
 es of identity\, memory and reconnection. Curated by Jesse King\, the exhi
 bit shares pieces from Toronto's Fine Art and Artifact Collection\, includ
 ing the photographic series The Emergence of Legend by Kent Monkman as wel
 l as contemporary art by Alexis Nanibush-Pamajewong\, Jake Kimble\, Kay Na
 djiwon\, Kiki Guerard\, Megan Feheley and Melissa Johns. Expect bold visua
 ls\, self-discovery\, and personal storytelling. Smoke Signals x Reflectio
 ns is a safe and affirming space for two-spirit\, Indigi-queer\, and gende
 r nonconforming artists.
LOCATION:401 Richmond Ltd\, 401 Richmond Street West\, Suite 128\, Toronto
 \, ON
URL:http://toronto.ca/marketgallery
X-SOURCE:City of Toronto Festivals & Events
END:VEVENT
