BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Roll Over Beethoven
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T150000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260419T150000
UID:fe37a84c9849e2c7324757d9d13f786a@toronto.ca
DESCRIPTION:Get ready for an unforgettable afternoon of music united by a 
 shared commitment to innovation and artistic expression! Join us for an ex
 traordinary concert featuring the iconic sounds of The Beatles and the tim
 eless compositions of Beethoven. Experience the magic of The Fab Four's re
 volutionary rock hits\, reimagined alongside the majestic power of Beethov
 en's masterpieces. Whether you're a fan of the classic harmonies of the Be
 atles or the dramatic brilliance of Beethoven\, this concert brings togeth
 er two musical worlds in a stunning fusion that will captivate your senses
 . Don't miss out on this one-of-a-kind event that celebrates the genius of
  these legendary artists\, where past and present collide in perfect harmo
 ny. Featuring guest artists Jonathan Crow\, Hezekiah Leung and Neil Deland
 .
LOCATION:Trinity-St. Paul's Centre\, 427 Bloor St W\, Toronto\, ON
URL:https://amiciensemble.com/roll-over-beethoven-2026/
X-SOURCE:City of Toronto Festivals & Events
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Native Edible Plants of Toronto Webinar
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T120000
UID:ea2860ffa879a76175eb3afb6469c8d2@toronto.ca
DESCRIPTION:Blueberries\, raspberries\, strawberries: they aren't just fou
 nd at the grocery store. There are native species of these fruits found in
  Toronto's ravines too! Join avid fruit gardener and City of Toronto Fores
 try staffer Steven Parkes for a webinar on Toronto's native and edible fru
 iting plants\, their ecological importance and where you might spot them i
 n our urban wilderness. You'll learn how adding these plants to your local
  landscapes and private gardens can enhance habitats\, support local wildl
 ife and pollinators\, while producing native fruits and nuts. Please note:
  this is not a foraging webinar. The focus will be on integrating native e
 dible plants into private gardens. Please snack responsibly.
LOCATION:On-line Event
URL:https://toronto.webex.com/webappng/sites/toronto/webinar/webinarSeries
 /register/cee2b157aad54ef6a36e8a38e5ad515b
X-SOURCE:City of Toronto Festivals & Events
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Steven Isserlis\, cello and Connie Shih\, piano
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260423T193000
UID:ab90329d354b34a5e1e5659326a15efd@toronto.ca
DESCRIPTION:These celebrated musicians are frequent collaborators\, captiv
 ating audiences at world-class venues like Wigmore Hall\, Carnegie Hall\, 
 and the Berlin Philharmonie. Beyond performance\, Isserlis is a passionate
  teacher\, author\, and broadcaster. As Sir John Barbirolli said\, "Steven
  Isserlis is a musician of immense talent and insight\, whose sound and in
 terpretation leave a deep and lasting impression." Their thoughtfully cura
 ted program highlights Isserlis's broad musical interests\, featuring the 
 Ritournelle by Czech composer Vítězslava Kaprálová alongside beloved c
 ello-piano repertoire gems. The program also includes Beethoven's 12 Varia
 tions on a Theme from The Magic Flute\, Op. 66 and Sonata No. 3 in A major
 \, Op. 69\, Schumann's 3 Fantasiestücke\, Op. 73\, and Kabalevsky's Sonat
 a. Experience an exceptional evening of profound musicianship and emotiona
 l depth from this outstanding duo.
LOCATION:Jane Mallett Theatre\, St. Lawrence Centre for the Arts\, 27 Fron
 t St E\, Toronto\, ON
URL:https://musictorontoconcerts.com/concerts/isserlis-shin
X-SOURCE:City of Toronto Festivals & Events
END:VEVENT
