BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Inscape: Scarborough's Shoreline Parks Exhibition
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260502T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260531T090000
UID:a3e9e4df1a007e9ece6f5e8384cf76df@toronto.ca
DESCRIPTION:Examine the visual and material tension between wilderness and
  human control along Scarborough's shoreline park system. Using traditiona
 l photographic techniques\, the work moves from representational landscape
  toward abstraction\, tracing how natural forces and urban intervention sh
 ape one another over time. The project draws from repeated visits to shore
 line parks\, beaches\, and wooded areas along the bluffs. About the Artist
  Chris is a Toronto-based photographer. Contemplative observation with a s
 trong graphic sensibility for image making\, have come to represent his ph
 otographic style. His personal work can be found in corporate and private 
 collections throughout North America and Europe.
LOCATION:Clark Centre for the Arts\, 191 Guildwood Pkwy\, Scarborough\, ON
URL:https://www.toronto.ca/explore-enjoy/history-art-culture/cultural-cent
 res-galleries/clark-centre-for-the-arts/
X-SOURCE:City of Toronto Festivals & Events
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Kerson Leong\, violin
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260503T151500
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260503T151500
UID:0bd9cb4946677f921573960af999e7d5@toronto.ca
DESCRIPTION:Winner of the prestigious International Menuhin Violin Competi
 tion\, Kerson Leong has been described as "not just one of Canada's greate
 st violinists but one of the greatest violinists\, period". He has perform
 ed with Brussels\, Oslo\, Royal Philharmonic and Istanbul\, Singapore\, To
 ronto\, Wuppertal and Montréal Symphony Orchestras. As a sought-after sol
 oist\, Kerson has appeared at Carnegie and Wigmore Halls\, Auditorium du L
 ouvre\, and National Center for the Performing Arts\, Beijing. He plays th
 e 'ex Bohrer\, Baumgartner' Guarneri del Gesu violin courtesy of Canimex I
 nc. Drummondville. His virtuosic recital includes violin works by Ysaÿe (
 Sonata No. 3 "Ballade" & Sonata No. 4 in E minor)\, Kreisler's Recitativo 
 and Scherzo\, and Bach's Chaconne from Partita No. 2.
LOCATION:Walter Hall\, University of Toronto\, 80 Queen's Park\, Toronto\,
  ON
URL:https://www.mooredaleconcerts.com
X-SOURCE:City of Toronto Festivals & Events
END:VEVENT
