 nforgettable musical voyage\, dancing and listening to classic hits from a
 rtists including: Toto\, Styx\, The Doobie Brothers\, Michael McDonald\, C
 hristopher Cross\, Kenny Loggins\, Steely Dan\, Boz Scaggs\, Player\, Litt
 le River Band\, Ambrosia. The El Mocambo is a legendary live music and ent
 ertainment venue in Toronto\, Canada\, that has hosted countless world-fam
 ous artists since it opened in 1948\, including The Rolling Stones\, Elvis
  Costello\, Blondie\, The Ramones\, and Stevie Ray Vaughan. The new El Moc
 ambo features state-of-the-art sound and lighting\, a recording studio\, a
 nd multiple floors for events and performances\, offering a modern\, VIP l
 ive music experience while maintaining its historical significance.
