BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hilary Hahn on Violin with Tom Poster on Piano
DTSTART;TZID=America/Toronto:20260521T190000
DTEND;TZID=America/Toronto:20260521T190000
UID:0e87ba8b1056cea73f880aee8428bd9e@toronto.ca
DESCRIPTION:Three-time Grammy Award-winning violinist Hilary Hahn melds ex
 pressive musicality and technical expertise with a diverse repertoire guid
 ed by artistic curiosity. She is currently artist-in-residence at both the
  Chicago Symphony Orchestra and London's Wigmore Hall\, and is co-founder 
 and vice president of artistic partnerships of the AI-music initiative Dee
 pmusic.AI. Hahn is a prolific and celebrated recording artist whose 21 fea
 ture albums on Decca\, Deutsche Grammophon\, and Sony have all opened in t
 he top ten of the Billboard charts. Enjoy her program of Maurice Ravel: Vi
 olin Sonata No. 2 in G Major\, M. 77\, Bun-Ching Lam: Solitude d'automne\,
  Lili Boulanger: Nocturne\, Maurice Ravel: Pièce en forme de Habanera\, M
 . 51\, Claude Debussy: Sonata for Violin and Piano in G Minor\, Scott Tixi
 er: new duo work (North American premiere)\, and Gabriel Fauré: Violin So
 nata No. 1 in A Major\, op. 13.
LOCATION:Koerner Hall\, Royal Conservatory of Music\, 273 Bloor St W\, Tor
 onto\, ON
URL:https://www.rcmusic.com/Tickets/Seats/299201
X-SOURCE:City of Toronto Festivals & Events
END:VEVENT
