DESCRIPTION:Their journey began in Poland\, where they won the prestigious
  Penderecki Prize at the 1986 National Chamber Music Competition in Łód
 ź. Since 1991\, they have served as Quartet-in-Residence at Wilfrid Lauri
 er University\, helping shape one of Canada's premier string programs. Kno
 wn for their dedication to contemporary music\, the Penderecki's have comm
 issioned and performed over 100 new works. We invite you to enjoy their pr
 ogram of Krzysztof Penderecki: String Quartet No. 3 Leaves of an Unwritten
  Diary and Franz Schubert: Quintet in C major for Two Cellos\, D. 956. Arr
 ive early to enjoy a pre-concert performance by Jacques Forestier\, violin
 .
LOCATION:Jane Mallett Theatre\, St. Lawrence Centre for the Arts\, 27 Fron
 t St E\, Toronto\, ON
